  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 7 airports right now. No engine anti-ice operations are currently flagged. Across base airports: 1 critical, 4 high, 12 medium, 22 normal. Key bases needing attention include London Luton (LTN/EGGW), Sofia (SOF/LBSF) and Venice Marco Polo (VCE/LIPZ); plus 2 other bases. 12 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is fog / freezing fog, mist and very low visibility  — most notably around Venice Marco Polo (VCE/LIPZ), London Luton (LTN/EGGW) and Sofia (SOF/LBSF). Network hotspots: Treviso Antonio Canova (TSF/LIPH), Trieste–Friuli Venezia Giulia (TRS/LIPQ), Venice Marco Polo (VCE/LIPZ), Shirak (LWN/UDSG), Tenerife Sur (TFS/GCTS) and 2 others. Primary drivers: RVR limitations, very low visibility and low cloud base. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 12 airports changed status, led by Treviso Antonio Canova (TSF/LIPH), Trieste–Friuli Venezia Giulia (TRS/LIPQ), Turku (TKU/EFTU) and 9 others.",
